description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of a team that has a real friendly, supportive and inclusive Trust with ethos and sense of community? If you answered ‘yes’ to the above, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals manages the&lt;strong&gt;temporary&lt;/strong&gt;work placement (bank) at The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust, and we are looking for an IT Support Services Technician to support the Health Informatics department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotherham Hospital which is situated just two miles south of Rotherham town centre, within proximity to the M1 and M18 motorways, six miles from Sheffield and close to Doncaster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade&lt;/strong&gt;: IT Support Services Technician (Band 5)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;Moorgate Road, Rotherham, S60 2UD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt;Health Informatics Department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay rate&lt;/strong&gt;: £13.79 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt;26/10/2020 to 11/12/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;: Full Time, 37.5hours/week to be worked Monday-Friday, 08.30am -16.30pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will cover several areas such as:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2nd line support of desktop/client applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports and maintains all PCs, Laptop, MCAs and peripherals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the field or remotely, provide basic triage of application issues, effecting or suggesting alternate routes to resolution for both technical and known application issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On a rotational basis, to act as incident manager for the IT Support Services team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and maintenance of desktop and mobile computer devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and maintenance of peripheral devices including but not limited to printers, scanners and barcode readers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnosis and resolution of hardware and software issues across the desktop environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configuration and deployment of computer and peripheral devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application of standard images as part of the deployment or support of computer equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patching of end user networked devices back to edge switches (port level).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide 2nd Level Support for hardware and software including the maintenance and re-building of computer equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deployment of new systems and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with 3rd party suppliers and maintainer’s e.g. Dell, HP, TPP, Connecting for Health Service Desk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log and report any service disruptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Service Desk Tools and Technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desktop operating systems and applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desktop/office applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data backup and recovery technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer and peripheral devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network protocols and technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server operating systems including Microsoft Server and/or Linux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HND (or equivalent) in a relevant technical subject (Essential)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree or equivalent occupational / professional qualification or experience (Essential)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Qualifications such as MCSE, MCP or A+ Certification (Desirable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prince2 or similar project management methodology (Desirable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ITIL Foundation level or higher (Desirable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and commitment, NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work this week, get paid next - Get paid the following Friday when you release your timesheets by 23:59 on Sunday.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get paid to take holiday! - Holiday is accrued during every shift you work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Statutory maternity/paternity (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our very own pension scheme called &#39;NHSP Stakeholder pension&#39; for eligible members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;...and we are part of the NHS family!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts do not have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 126,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades, and specialities, saving the NHS over £70 million each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register today for various flexible working options and long-term placement opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
